rComments: His section (respiratory) shouldn't be challenging but he keeps going too far ahead with his explanations and his lectures are really jumbled and all over the place. Also has a French accent, which was kind of hard to understand.

A very boring lecturer. Always speaks in a monotone droning voice, and basically just reads off of the slides. Easily the worst prof to teach in the PSL classes, and one of the worst I've had at U of T

My favourite lecturer in PSL301. He taught the respiratory section and it ended up being my favourite part of the whole course. He is very clear with what we need to know, explains concepts clearly, and all his test questions are fair.
